<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It is a small technical problem that you proba=
bly cannot=C2=A0<em>just=C2=A0</em>do this. You cannot=C2=A0<em>just=C2=A0<=
/em>issue stock that is like =E2=80=9Cthis is the stock with my name on it,=
 go buy it!=E2=80=9D You can=E2=80=99t start a company and take it public t=
o be <em>purely </em>a meme stock.=C2=A0I cannot give you a really crisp=C2=
=A0explanation of why not. I am not aware of any provision of US securities=
 law that is like =E2=80=9Cif you raise money for a public company, it has =
to do something, or at least try.=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s just, you know. If =
you say =E2=80=9CI am launching a company with my name on it, and that=E2=
=80=99s it,=E2=80=9D then underwriters probably will not want to work with =
you, and lawyers will be confused writing the prospectus, and eventually th=
e US Securities and Exchange Commission will have to sign off on the prospe=
ctus and will find reasons not to.=C2=A0</p>
