<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Donald Trump has sued two co-founders of his n=
ewly public Trump Media &amp; Technology Group Corp., claiming they set the=
 company up improperly and shouldn=E2=80=99t get any stock in it.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the latest legal skirmish over who gets how=
 much of the hot but flailing meme stock, Trump alleges that Andy Litinsky =
and Wes Moss violated an agreement about the setup and don=E2=80=99t deserv=
e their 8.6% stake, currently valued at $606 million.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The lawsuit, which was filed on March 24 in Fl=
orida state court and hasn=E2=80=99t previously been reported, comes after =
the pair brought their own suit against the former president in Delaware Ch=
ancery Court over their promised stake in the social media company.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/34916007.287354/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVu=
dHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JtY19DNndGM1pEVS92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B6aadf335" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">the complaint</a>, which basically alleges that Litinsky=
 and Moss =E2=80=94=C2=A0=E2=80=9Cformer contestants on President Trump=E2=
=80=99s famous television show,=C2=A0<em>The Apprentice</em>=E2=80=9D =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0did an incompetent job of launching TMTG=E2=80=99s media busine=
ss and finding a merger partner. And, fine, I can believe that. (They=C2=A0=
did manage to find <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click=
/34916007.287354/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy=
0xMzU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB956ae6e7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">an <em>illegal=C2=A0</em=
>merger partner</a>.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I think that the broader point here is tha=
t Litinsky and Moss were hired to set up TMTG=E2=80=99s rather small and sp=
eculative=C2=A0<em>business</em>, and it is absurd to reward them with 8.6%=
 of DJT=E2=80=99s much larger=C2=A0<em>meme stock</em>. My favorite part of=
 the complaint is not actually in the complaint, but in the exhibit at the =
end, in which Trump=E2=80=99s lawyers reproduce the Services Agreement betw=
een him and Litinsky and Moss. It just has a very small-business feel, you =
know? Their role included =E2=80=9Censuring that TMG becomes an established=
 entity registered under the laws of the state of Delaware =E2=80=A6=C2=A0a=
nd creating and implementing a strategic plan to identify, exploit, and com=
mercialize targeted media and technology opportunities in social media, int=
ernet infrastructure, podcast, digital streaming, mobile apps, book publica=
tion, and television production.=E2=80=9D There was not much vision; their =
job was to set up the company and look around for something for it to do.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A schedule to the agreement lists =E2=80=9Cgui=
delines for reimbursable expenses.=E2=80=9D Litinsky and Moss were entitled=
 to reimbursement for =E2=80=9Ceconomy, coach or supersaver fares=E2=80=9D =
on flights and trains, though =E2=80=9C21-day advance purchase is expected,=
 when possible.=E2=80=9D Reasonable hotel bills were reimbursable, "where u=
nder $150.00 per night is typically reasonable for most cities.=E2=80=9D La=
undry and dry cleaning were =E2=80=9Cnot normally reimbursed for planned tr=
ips of less than 1 week.=E2=80=9D They had to submit receipts for =E2=80=9C=
any individual expenditure of $10.00 or more.=E2=80=9D This is not Facebook=
 Inc.=E2=80=99s charter, is what I am saying here. This is =E2=80=9Cset up =
a small business for me, but don=E2=80=99t spend more than $150 a night on =
hotels.=E2=80=9D And now they might get $600 million!</p>
