<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Hunterbrook</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/34916007.287354/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMDIvYS1oZWRnZS1mdW5kLXRoYXQtcy1hbHNvLWEtbmV3c3BhcGVyP=
2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MDMyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1u=
ZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQwMyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cBd099d31e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">wrote yesterday</a> that Hunterbrook, th=
e hedge fund that is also a newspaper, is a sort of salary arbitrage. Hunte=
rbrook Media is a news organization that employs reporters to write investi=
gative stories, and then it gives those stories to Hunterbrook Capital, its=
 affiliated hedge fund, to make trades before the stories are published. If=
 the stories are right and market-moving, then the hedge fund will make mon=
ey, which it can use to pay for the news organization. I wrote: =E2=80=9CIt=
 is expensive to hire hedge fund analysts to investigate companies all over=
 the world. It is cheaper to hire journalists!=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Hunterbrook also has another, much funnier=
 expense arbitrage. It goes like this:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are a hedge fund conducting due=
 diligence on a company, you will probably want to speak to experts. You mi=
ght pay an expert-network firm to put you in touch with industry experts. Y=
ou might engage consultants to evaluate the business. If you think the comp=
any might have legal issues, you will talk to specialist lawyers to help ev=
aluate those issues. In each case, you will call up the experts and say =E2=
=80=9Chi, I work at Hedge Fund X, we are evaluating Company Y, and we=E2=80=
=99d like to get your views.=E2=80=9D And those experts will probably say s=
omething like =E2=80=9Csure, that will be $2,000 per hour with a $10,000 mi=
nimum.=E2=80=9D And you=E2=80=99ll say =E2=80=9Cyes perfect send an invoice=
 to our billing department.=E2=80=9D You have a budget for this stuff.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are a newspaper reporter invest=
igating a company, you will probably want to speak to experts =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0industry experts, lawyers, etc. You will call up the experts and say =E2=
=80=9Chi, I am a reporter for the Z Daily News, I am writing a story about =
Company Y, and I=E2=80=99d like to get your views.=E2=80=9D And those exper=
ts might say something like =E2=80=9Csure, I would love to get my name in t=
he paper, here is a pithy quote.=E2=80=9D Or they might say =E2=80=9CI don=
=E2=80=99t want to be quoted, but on background =E2=80=A6=E2=80=9D and then=
 tell you stuff. Or occasionally =E2=80=94=C2=A0but not that often =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0they might say =E2=80=9Csure I=E2=80=99ll talk to you, but I=E2=80=
=99ll need $2,000 per hour with a $10,000 minimum.=E2=80=9D In that case, y=
ou will say =E2=80=9Coh no, you don=E2=80=99t understand, I am a=C2=A0<em>j=
ournalist</em>, it is unethical for me to pay sources.=E2=80=9D And then th=
ey=E2=80=99ll probably hang up, which is fine; you=E2=80=99ll call someone =
else who wants to be quoted.</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You see the arbitrage! Hunterbrook=E2=80=99s c=
onsulting budget is probably smaller than that of other hedge funds.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yesterday Hunterbrook Media published <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34916007.287354/aHR0cHM6L=
y9obnRyYnJrLmNvbS91d20v/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB21d89451" itemprop=3D"Stor=
yLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; t=
ext-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-co=
lor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">its firs=
t big investigation</a>, of United Wholesale Mortgage, alleging that =E2=80=
=9CUWM=E2=80=99s conduct could constitute fraud and run afoul of laws passe=
d after 2008 to protect borrowers.=E2=80=9D Hunterbrook Capital shorted UWM=
=E2=80=99s stock. If you want to figure out if a company=E2=80=99s conduct =
runs afoul of laws, one thing you might do is call up a lawyer and say =E2=
=80=9Chey is this conduct legal?=E2=80=9D If you are a hedge fund and you d=
o that, the lawyer will send you a bill. If you are a media organization, m=
aybe she won=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so in fact I heard yesterday from a lawyer=
 who got that call (actually email) from Hunterbrook, and who replied to th=
e effect of =E2=80=9Csure here are my rates,=E2=80=9D and they replied to t=
he effect of =E2=80=9Cno our ethics policy does not allow us to pay sources=
.=E2=80=9D From <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34=
916007.287354/aHR0cHM6Ly9obnRyYnJrLmNvbS9hYm91dC11cy8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a=
23cB89859553" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bla=
nk" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; bac=
kground-color: #ccc;">Hunterbrook=E2=80=99s website</a>:=C2=A0</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">At Hunterbrook Media, we abide by the five tra=
ditional standards re: source relationships, adapted from the New York Time=
s:</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>1)=E2=80=83Financial Interactions:</st=
rong> Don=CA=BCt pay sources, and don=CA=BCt let them pay you (or pay for y=
ou).=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The lawyer replied to the effect of =E2=80=9Cm=
an you are not fooling me, when investment firms call me for analysis I cha=
rge them.=E2=80=9D They did not hire him. Also he forwarded me their exchan=
ge, commenting: =E2=80=9CNormally, conversations in search of legal counsel=
 are subject to confidentiality obligations under legal ethics, but I don=
=E2=80=99t see how they can claim they were seeking legal advice or that th=
e inquiry was confidential. They viewed me as a =E2=80=98source.=E2=80=99=
=E2=80=9D It=E2=80=99s true! They weren=E2=80=99t looking to hire him as a =
lawyer, but to interview him as a source, so he has no confidentiality obli=
gations to them. If they had paid him, he would.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In other Hunterbrook news, it=C2=A0<a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34916007.287354/aHR0cHM6Ly9ob=
nRyYnJrLmNvbS91d20v/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC21d89451" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">disclosed ye=
sterday</a>=C2=A0that its =E2=80=9Cnonprofit affiliate has entered an agree=
ment with [Boies Schiller Flexner LLP]=C2=A0in exploration of a class actio=
n lawsuit against UWM seeking restitution for homebuyers.=E2=80=9D The <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34916007.287354/aHR0cH=
M6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3I3Qkc1MzBNY=
UJzay92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfbf5a635" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsco=
pe=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration=
: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; =
border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">class action complaint=
</a> was filed yesterday:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Over the past three years, UWM has issued near=
ly $39 billion in mortgages through =E2=80=9Cindependent=E2=80=9D brokers <=
em>who refer 99% of their business</em> to UWM. And during last year alone,=
 more than 8,000 so-called =E2=80=9Cindependent=E2=80=9D brokers funneled 9=
9% or more of their mortgages to UWM, worth at least $11.7 billion. In shor=
t, those brokers are not shopping around to other lenders. They are not see=
king the best prices for their principals. They are instead captive to UWM.=
 Through a series of intentional and illegal practices, UWM has thus corrup=
ted a large swath of =E2=80=9Cindependent=E2=80=9D brokers and turned them =
into the functional equivalent of the =E2=80=9Cloan officers=E2=80=9D that =
retail financial institutions use. These corrupted brokers are in essence e=
mployees in the UWM enterprise. And while doing that, both UWM and the corr=
upted brokers have concealed this fact from consumers who have been led to =
believe their =E2=80=9Cindependent=E2=80=9D brokers are working for them an=
d shopping around to multiple lenders.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The consequences to UWM=E2=80=99s borrowers ha=
ve been devastating. UWM rarely offered the best available pricing througho=
ut the past four years and routinely charged fees that substantially exceed=
ed their competitors=E2=80=99 offerings to the tune of billions of dollars.=
 While UWM=E2=80=99s borrowers believed that their =E2=80=9Cindependent=E2=
=80=9D brokers were working for them, in reality, UWM induced thousands of =
these brokers to participate in their funneling scheme and enterprise by su=
ccessfully infiltrating and corrupting their duties to the Plaintiffs and t=
he class.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Presumably Boies Schiller plans to get paid.</=
p>
