<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My stupid <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/34916007.287354/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDYtMjcvc2lsaWNvbi12YWxsZXktaXMtb24tZHJ1Z3M_Y21wa=
WQ9QkJEMDQwMzI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3Ns=
ZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDAzJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB5226d7eb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">story of private credit</a> is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Once upon a time, there were insuranc=
e companies, which had long-dated liabilities (annuities, life insurance) a=
nd funded them by buying and holding corporate bonds. This was a boring bus=
iness: You bought the bonds, you literally clipped literal paper coupons to=
 collect interest, and eventually the bonds matured and you got your money =
back in time to pay your liabilities.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5p=
x;">Then Bill Gross, a guy clipping coupons in the bond department at an in=
surance company, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3=
4916007.287354/aHR0cHM6Ly91cy5tYWNtaWxsYW4uY29tL2Jvb2tzLzk3ODEyNTAxMjA4NTQv=
dGhlYm9uZGtpbmc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd294ab86" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">invented bond </=
a><em><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34916007.287=
354/aHR0cHM6Ly91cy5tYWNtaWxsYW4uY29tL2Jvb2tzLzk3ODEyNTAxMjA4NTQvdGhlYm9uZGt=
pbmc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCd294ab86" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">trading</a>.=C2=A0</em>It t=
urned out that you could make more money by buying undervalued bonds and se=
lling overvalued ones than you could by just buying and holding to maturity=
.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">This became a big business that =
was entirely separate from insurance: People (prominently including Gross) =
set up big bond investment companies that actively managed bond portfolios =
on behalf of clients, insurers and endowments and mutual funds and others.<=
/li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Over time, the bond market became=
=C2=A0more=C2=A0<em>efficient:=C2=A0</em>All this liquidity and competition=
 probably lowered borrowing costs for companies.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin=
-bottom: 5px;">At some point, people realized that, now, you can actually m=
ake more money by making loans and hold them to maturity: You collect an il=
liquidity premium for buying debt that doesn=E2=80=99t trade, you structure=
 loans to meet borrowers=E2=80=99 needs so you can charge them a bit more t=
han the bond market, and maybe you face a bit less competition. And so priv=
ate credit grew up as an alternative to the bond market.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A problem with this business is that, if you have =
outside investors, they might ask for their money back at any time, and if =
you mostly own illiquid private=C2=A0loans that you can=E2=80=99t sell, tha=
t=E2=80=99s a problem.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">What you wa=
nt is a bunch of actuarially predictable, long-dated liabilities. Like an i=
nsurance company.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">So you buy an in=
surance company.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The result is ins=
urance companies with long-dated liabilities that are funded by buying and =
holding private debt.=C2=A0</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Someho=
w this is not as boring a job as it was in Step 1? And it pays better.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This story is wrong in many details, and dumb,=
=C2=A0but it does seem sort of directionally accurate. <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/34916007.287354/aHR0cHM6Ly9oYnIub3JnLz=
IwMTQvMDYvaG93LXRvLXN1Y2NlZWQtaW4tYnVzaW5lc3MtYnktYnVuZGxpbmctYW5kLXVuYnVuZ=
Gxpbmc/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBce6ba302" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
